import React from 'react'; import Navbar from '../../components/Admin/Navbar'; import { Container, Row, Col, Card } from 'react-bootstrap'; import { Pie, Bar } from 'react-chartjs-2'; const AdminDashboard = () => { // Dummy data for demonstration const totalPatients = 1000; const totalDoctors = 50; const patientIncrease = 20; // Assume 20 new patients const doctorIncrease = 2; // Assume 2 new doctors // Data for pie chart const pieChartData = { labels: ['Male', 'Female'], datasets: [{ data: [40, 60], // Dummy data for male and female percentages backgroundColor: ['#007bff', '#ffc107'], }] }; // Data for bar graph const barGraphData = { labels: ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun'], datasets: [{ label: 'Patients', backgroundColor: '#28a745', borderColor: '#28a745', borderWidth: 1, hoverBackgroundColor: '#218838', hoverBorderColor: '#218838', data: [65, 59, 80, 81, 56, 55], // Dummy data for patient counts per month }] }; return (
Total Patients

{totalPatients}
New Patients (Today)

+{patientIncrease}
Total Doctors

{totalDoctors}
New Doctors (Today)

+{doctorIncrease}
); }; export default AdminDashboard;
